  "prompt": "Will I get disability benefits for govt jobs after a bike accident?",
  "response": "Whether you can receive disability benefits for government jobs after a bike accident depends on several factors, including the specific policies of your employer, the nature and severity of your injuries, and whether you meet the criteria for disability benefits under relevant laws and regulations.\n\nHere are the key steps you should consider:\n\n1. **Documentation of Injury**: Ensure you have proper medical documentation detailing the extent of your injuries and how they affect your ability to work.\n\n2. **Employer's Disability Policy**: Check your employer's policies regarding disability benefits. Government jobs often have specific guidelines and procedures for applying for benefits.\n\n3. **Eligibility Criteria**: Review the eligibility criteria for disability benefits, which may include the length of employment, the nature of the injury, and how it impacts your capacity to perform your job duties.\n\n4. **Application Process**: Follow the necessary application process. This may involve filling out forms, providing medical records, and possibly undergoing assessments by medical professionals designated by your employer.\n\n5. **Legal Assistance**: If you're having trouble navigating the process, you may want to consult with a lawyer or an advocate who specializes in disability claims to help you understand your rights and options.\n\n6. **Consider Social Security Disability**: If your injuries are severe and long-lasting, you may also want to consider applying for Social Security Disability Insurance (SSDI) if you meet the criteria set by the Social Security Administration (SSA).\n\nMake sure to act promptly, as there may be deadlines for applying for benefits after an accident.",
